The paper deals with recommendation systems, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed algorithm involves matrix factorization, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm also uses gradient boosted trees, which is a popular method in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses regularization and model complexity, which are topics in data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper experiments on recommendation datasets that involve movies, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) as well.
